  <bioghist id="aspace_330b34ae1f8c4aa0f055aa3cc097d4a9">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>John Southworth moved from Herkimer County, New York to Dryden, Tompkins County, New York with his father, Thomas Southworth, in 1806. He became a large landholder and one of the wealthiest men in Tompkins County.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_e943f4ca415c1bbe32da8237b84f98ea">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes land deeds from New York, Wisconsin, Michigan, Pennsylvania, Iowa, and Indiana; mortgages and bonds; letters patent; bank-related correspondence; legal correspondence; ledger sheets; survey bills; lists of leases and purchases; stock certificate books; checkbook; and diary.</p>  </scopecontent>
